         </tr>
   </table>
      <hr>
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <p>Chronological information identifying the days and/or times an item is available or
         accessible. Used primarily in records for electronic resources.
      </p>
      <p>When displayed or printed as a note, hours, etc. information is in some instances
                     preceded by an introductory term or phrase that is generated based on the first
                     indicator value.      </p>
      <hr>
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> INDICATORS
      </h4>
      <div class="indicator"><strong>First Indicator - Display constant controller</strong> <div class="description">Controls the generation of a display constant preceding the note.
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong># - Hours</strong> <div class="description">Used to generate the display constant <em>Hours:</em>.
                  <div class="example">
                     <table width="100%">
                        <tr>
                           <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>307</strong></td>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>M-F, 9:30am-3:30pm, USA EST.
                           </td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong>8 - No display constant generated</strong> </div>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="indicator"><strong>Second Indicator - Undefined</strong> <div class="description">Undefined and contains a blank (#).
            </div>
      </div>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> SUBFIELD CODES
      </h4>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$a - Hours</strong> <div class="description">Days and/or hours an item is available or accessible. Informal references to the
                              A.M. and P.M. time references as well as time zone can be given in this subfield
                              if required.
         </div>
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>307</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>M-F, 9AM-10PM.
                  </td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>307</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>Tu-F, 10-6; Sa, 1-5, USA PST.
                  </td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>307</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>M, 8:30-6:00; Tu, 8:30-7:00; W-F, 8:30-6:00;<strong>$b</strong>not available on weekends.
                  </td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>307</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>8#</strong><strong>$a</strong>8:00 p.m., Tu-F; 5:00 and 9:00 p.m., Sa; 2:00 and 7:00
                                             p.m., Su (all times, EST).
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$b - Additional information</strong> <div class="description">Additional information pertaining to the hours of availability of the item.</div>
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>307</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>M-F, 6:30am-9:00pm (EST);<strong>$b</strong>with brief interruptions for periodic update/backup of
                                             data.
                  </td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>307</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>Daily, 7am-7pm;<strong>$b</strong>text files only.
                  </td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>307</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>M-F, 6:30 AM to 9:30 PM, Sa, 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM, Su,
                                             1:00 PM to 5:00 PM;<strong>$b</strong>closed on national holidays (all times are EST or
                                             ESDT).
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$6 - Linkage</strong> <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                                       Subfields</a></em>.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$8 - Field link and sequence number</strong> 
        <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                                       Subfields</a></em>.
        </div>
   </div>
      <hr>
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Punctuation</strong> -  Field 307 ends with a period unless another mark of punctuation is present. In subfield
                     $a, a comma (,) separates the hours information from the days of the week
                     information. If subfield $a is followed by a subfield $b, the
                     subfield ends in a semicolon (;).
      </div>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Abbreviations</strong> -  For records in English, the following abbreviations may be used for the days of the
                     week:
         <div class="table">
            <table>
               <tr>
                  <td width="171" align="left" valign="top"><u>Days of the week</u></td>
                  <td width="229" align="left" valign="top"><u>Abbreviation</u></td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Sunday</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Su</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Monday</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">M</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Tuesday</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Tu</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Wednesday</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">W</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Thursday</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Th</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Friday</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">F</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Saturday</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Sa</td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Display Constant</strong> - Introductory term <em>Hours:</em> is not carried in the MARC record. It may be system
                     generated as a display constant associated with the first indicator value.
         <div class="table">
            <table>
               <tr>
                  <td width="167" align="left" valign="top"><u>First indicator</u></td>
                  <td width="235" align="left" valign="top"><u>Display constant</u></td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">#</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Hours:</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">8</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left"><em>[no display constant]</em></td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
